{
    "word": "Heretic",
    "definitions": [
        "One who holds to a heresy; one who believes some doctrine contrary to the established faith or prevailing religion.",
        "One who having made a profession of Christian belief, deliberately and pertinaciously refuses to believe one or more of the articles of faith"
    ],
    "examples": [
        "A man that is an heretic, after the first and second admonition, reject."
    ],
    "etymology": "[L. haereticus, Gr. h. See Heresy.]"
